<p>EDA of the categorical variables was done next. The results can be seen in the figure below. From these results, we can see that there is not a significant correlation between the reason for wanting a loan and whether it was defaulted. However, the amount lost on the loan for loans that defaulted was significantly higher for ‘DebtCon’ than ‘HomeImp’. For job type, people with the job classes ‘Sales’ and ‘Self’ were much more likely to default on their loan. The job class ‘Self’ also had a significantly higher average loss amount on the loan than the other job categories.</p>
