<p>Finally, float variables were explored. I will not print all the results, but an example of the output can be seen in the figure below. Among float variables there appeared to be strong correlation between loans being defaulted and the following variables: DEROG (derogatory marks on credit card), DELINQ (delinquencies on current credit report), and DEBTINC (debt to income ratio). These variables all had positive correlations with defaulting on the loans. There also appeared to be strong correlations between the amount lost on the loan and the following variables: MORTDUE (outstanding mortgage balance), VALUE (value of the house), DELINQ (delinquencies on current credit report), CLNO (number of credit lines), and DEBTINC (debt to income ratio). Again, these variables all had positive correlation with the amount defaulted.</p>
